      "raw_text": "SEATTLE, Sept. 24.-Insisting\nthat it was an unwarranted inter\nference with his determination to\nserve a Jail sentence as martyr\nto the fight the socialists are max\ning for the privilege of street\nspeaking, DIR. Herman +. Titus was\nreleased from the city Jail. His\nattorney, C. A. Riddle, paid the\namount of the fine and costs to Sc\ncure his release."
